Train and Test Set¶

In [5]:
ds_train = tfds.load(name="beans", split="train")
ds_test = tfds.load(name="beans", split="test")

Convert data into numpy array¶

In [7]:
train_images = np.array([example['image'].numpy() for example in ds_train])
train_labels = np.array([example['label'].numpy() for example in ds_train])

test_images = np.array([example['image'].numpy() for example in ds_test])
test_labels = np.array([example['label'].numpy() for example in ds_test])

Normalize¶

In [12]:
train_images = train_images.astype('float32')
test_images = test_images.astype('float32')

train_images /= 255
test_images /= 255

Train Convolutional Neural Network¶

In [17]:
from tensorflow import keras
model = keras.Sequential([
    keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu', input_shape=(500, 500, 3)),
    keras.layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    
    keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),
    
    keras.layers.Flatten(),
    keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(3, activation='softmax')
])

model.compile(optimizer='adam',
              loss=keras.losses.SparseCategoricalCrossentropy(),
              metrics=['accuracy'])

model.fit(train_images, train_labels, epochs=5, batch_size=32)

classes = ["Angular_Leaf_Spot","Bean_Rust","Healthy"]
In [22]:
def plot_sample(X, y, index):
    plt.figure(figsize = (15,2))
    plt.imshow(X[index])
    plt.xlabel(classes[y[index]])
